<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Barcelona Unbeaten in Champions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Barcelona kept its Champions League record perfect Wednesday  
with a 4-2 victory over Fiorentina of Italy. 
</P>
<P>
	Rivaldo of Brazil scored twice late in the game for Barcelona,  
with Luis Figo and Luis Enrique providing early goals in the second 
round of the schedule. 
</P>
<P>
	Defending champion Manchester United, after a disappointing 0-0  
tie in its opener a week ago, routed Sturm Graz 3-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Olympique Marseille of France won its second straight game,  
joining Barcleona and FC Porto of Portugal as the only clubs in the 
32-team competition with a perfect 2-0 record. 
</P>
<P>
	Olympique Marseille defeated Croatia Zagreb 2-1. Porto won its  
second match on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Other results Wednesday: Lazio of Rome 2, Dynamo Kiev 1; Maribor  
0, Bayer Leverkusen 2; Arsenal 3, AIK Solna 1; Barcelona 4, 
Fiorentina 2; Borussia Dortmund 3, Boavista 1; Rosenborg 2, 
Feyenoord 2; Strum Graz 0, Manchester United 3. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
