<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dell Targets Consumer Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROUND ROCK, Texas (AP) -- Dell Computer Corp. took another step  
Wednesday in its targeting of the consumer market, unveiling a new 
advertising campaign, high-speed cable Internet access and a line 
of colorful notebook computers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Round Rock, Texas-based direct seller of computers is trying  
to branch out beyond its core market of selling PCs to business 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
	Janet Mountain, Dell vice president and general manager of its  
consumer business, said the new campaign is designed to convince 
consumers the giant computer maker can handle all of their 
computing needs. 
</P>
<P>
	The new television and print advertisements will begin running  
Saturday. They are short on machine specifications and long on 
generalities of benefits from using computers. 
</P>
<P>
	The company also announced a new line of Inspiron notebook  
computers with more color -- blue or gray. 
</P>
<P>
	Dell joined with Excite@Home to offer the high-speed cable  
Internet service. It will use products from MusicMatch and Diamond 
Multimedia to offer a new digital music PC jukebox. 
</P>
<P>
	Dell calls the new campaign Dell4me. In July, the computer maker  
announced a new Internet service, called Dellnet. 
</P>
<P>
	In the past year, Dell has moved up from seventh to fourth in  
its share of the consumer market, according to Ziff Davis 
Infobeads. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
