<HEADLINE> Circuit Board Maker Heads to Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NAMPA, Idaho (AP) -- Idaho circuit board manufacturer MCMS will  
open a 112,000 square foot plant early next year in Monterrey, 
Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Downing, president and chief operating officer of MCMS,  
said Tuesday the expansion makes economic sense because labor costs 
are lower in Mexico and potential buyers in Silicon Valley are 
comfortable with products from there. 
</P>
<P>
	MCMS, based in Nampa, Idaho, the company quadrupled the size of  
its Malaysia operations this year. The company also has 
manufacturing operations here, in North Carolina and in Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mexico site probably will open with about 50 employees,  
Downing said, and will do simple manufacturing processes. 
</P>
<P>
	The company employs about 1,150 people in Nampa and about 2,050  
around the world. 
</P>
<P>
	MCMS formerly was known as Micron Custom Manufacturing Services.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
