<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Utah Doctor Charged With 5 Murders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- A doctor has been arrested and charged  
with killing five elderly patients by giving them massive doses of 
morphine and other drugs. 
</P>
<P>
	Dr. Robert Weitzel was arrested on five first-degree murder  
charges Tuesday night as he got off his private plane in Bay City, 
Texas. He was booked at the Matagorda County Jail and posted 
$100,000 bond. 
</P>
<P>
	The five patients died between December 1995 and January 1996.  
At the time, Weitzel was the director of a geriatric-psychiatric 
unit run by Houston-based Horizons Mental Health Management Inc. at 
the Davis Hospital and Medical Center in Layton. 
</P>
<P>
	Only one other patient died in the two years the unit was open.  
</P>
<P>
	``It was our determination that five of the six deaths were the  
direct result of the administration of the drug morphine, which was 
administered or caused to be administered by Dr. Weitzel,'' Davis 
County Attorney Melvin Wilson said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Weitzel's attorney, Peter Stirba, said his client is innocent.  
</P>
<P>
	``It is unfortunate that difficult questions of medical judgment  
are now the subject of a criminal prosecution,'' Stirba said in a 
statement. 
</P>
<P>
	Weitzel now practices primarily at Matagorda General Hospital in  
Bay City, a city about 75 miles southwest of Houston. He also 
shares an office at the Red Butte Clinic near the University of 
Utah. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
