<HEADLINE> Bruins Sign P.J. Axelsson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Left wing P.J. Axelsson signed a two-year contract  
with the Boston Bruins on Wednesday, the team said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're glad this has been resolved prior to the season's start,  
and we expect P.J. in Boston in the next couple of days to join his 
teammates for practice,'' Bruins president and general manager 
Harry Sinden said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bruins gave no other contract details.  
</P>
<P>
	Axelsson, 24, is entering his third season with the Bruins. The  
6-foot-1 Swede was the Bruins' seventh pick, and the 177th overall 
pick, in the 1995 NHL entry draft. 
</P>
<P>
	He played four seasons with Frolunda Goteborg of the Swedish  
Elite League, scoring 36 goals and 21 assists in 105 games before 
joining the Bruins in 1997-98. 
</P>
<P>
	During his rookie year, Axelson was eighth in scoring among  
rookies with eight goals and 19 assists. Last year, he had seven 
goals and 10 assists in 77 games. 
  	   	
</P>
