<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Wednesday, Sept. 22, 1999    	

</P>
<P>
	Blue Chips Fall; Dow Ends Off 74.40  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks fell today, extending  
yesterday's 225-point plunge by the Dow Jones industrial average 
and pushing that index to its lowest level in three months. But 
strength among technology shares and smaller-company issues 
bolstered the broad market, with the Nasdaq compsite index rising 
back toward record territory. The Dow fell 74.40 to 10,524.07, 
about 800 points below its record-high close of 11,326.04 set Aug. 
25. In the technology group, 3Com rose 1 5/16 to 28 5/8 as the most 
active Nasdaq issue after the maker of computer network products 
and Palm Pilot organizers topped Wall Street forecasts with its 
profit report late yesterday. The Nasdaq rose 37.07 to 2,858.17, 
about 30 points shy of a new high. 

</P>
