<HEADLINE> Knicks Hire Mills As Executive VP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Knicks hired Steve Mills as  
executive vice president of franchise operations Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mills, who spent the last 15 years with the NBA as senior vice  
president of basketball and player development, will be in charge 
of the Knicks' business operations. His duties will include 
financial planning, business affairs, marketing, community 
relations and game-night operations. 
</P>
<P>
	Mills and general manager Scott Layden will report to Dave  
Checketts, president and chief executive officer of Madison Square 
Garden. 
  	   	
