<HEADLINE> Upcoming Celebrity Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays    	

</P>
<P>
	When Bryant Gumbel begins his job as co-host of ``The Early  
Show,'' he will have 32-year-old Jane Clayson as his partner. 
Clayson has reported for ``World News Tonight'' and other ABC 
broadcasts since 1997, covering Bob Dole's presidential campaign 
and the O.J. Simpson civil trial. The search for Gumbel's co-host 
was so closely watched that it was dubbed ``Operation Glass 
Slipper'' within the television industry. Gumbel, who was born on 
Sept. 29, 1948, begins his new duties on Nov. 1. A storefront 
studio is being constructed across from Central Park for the CBS 
show. 

</P>
<P>
	Gwyneth Paltrow stars with Matt Damon in the new film, ``The  
Talented Mr. Ripley.'' Damon plots to insinuate himself into the 
lush life of playboy Jude Law and his girlfriend, played by 
Paltrow, who was born on Sept. 27, 1972. Her previous films include 
``Shakespeare in Love'' and ``Sliding Doors.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Janeane Garofalo isn't one of Hollywood's most fashionable  
actresses -- and she's proud to say she just doesn't care. ``There's 
a let-them-eat-cake quality to fashion that bothers me,'' Garofalo 
said. ``I can't in good conscience read in the paper about a 
Bosnian rape camp and then put on an $8,000 Versace dress.'' 
Garofalo, who was born on Sept. 28, 1964, was criticized for 
wearing a plain, off-the-rack dress to the 1996 Emmy Awards. 

</P>
<P>
