<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Siegfried and Roy Going Hollywood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Siegfried and Roy -- Las Vegas entertainment  
icons for nearly 30 years -- are going Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
	The famous illusionists are scheduled to attend Thursday's  
unveiling of their honorary star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame. 
They'll be accompanied by two of their rare white tiger cubs, Magic 
and Illusion. 
</P>
<P>
	Later in the day, the two will attend the world premiere of  
their IMAX movie, ``Siegfried and Roy: The Magic Box,'' in Los 
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	The show opens to the general public Oct. 1 in cities across  
America. It chronicles their rise in show business and their work 
in helping save endangered white lions and tigers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Hollywood star will be the 2,144th on the famous boulevard.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
