<DOCNO> APW19990922.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-22 11:40:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> political </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McCain Tells GOP To Let Buchanan Go </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- John McCain said today that Pat Buchanan's  
``own rhetoric'' indicates that he already has left the Republican 
Party and that, despite the political implications, it is time for 
the GOP to let him go. 
</P>
<P>
	Buchanan has said he is ``dead serious'' in considering leaving  
the Republican Party to seek the Reform Party's presidential 
nomination. He is expected to announce his decision next month. 
</P>
<P>
	Republican leaders fear a third-party bid by Buchanan would  
siphon votes from the GOP nominee and put a Democrat back in the 
White House. 
</P>
<P>
	Jim Nicholson, chairman of the Republican National Committee,  
has met with Buchanan. Other GOP presidential candidates have tread 
softly on the matter. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm fully aware of the political implications of a Buchanan  
third-party candidacy but regardless of what the polls show our 
party must stand on principle,'' McCain said. 
</P>
<P>
	McCain said in a statement that it appears that Buchanan already  
has made his decision. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's evident to me by Pat Buchanan's own rhetoric that he's  
left the Republican Party,'' the Arizona senator said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Defeating Hitler's Germany and Tojo's Japan was a very noble  
cause and I would not want any Republican to think otherwise, or 
any American for that matter.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In his new book, ``A Republic, Not an Empire,'' Buchanan  
contended that Adolf Hitler was not a direct threat to the United 
States after 1940 and his ambitions for conquest were toward the 
east, not the west. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hitler's real ambitions lay in carving out an empire in the  
east ... He had given up the idea of global empire,'' said 
Buchanan, a frequent critic of U.S. intervention overseas. 
</P>
<P>
	But, Buchanan said the United States was right to fight in  
Europe after Germany declared war. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
