<HEADLINE> Ind. Police Find Frozen Woman, Baby </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- The frozen bodies of a woman and an infant  
wrapped in blue plastic tarps were found Wednesday stuffed inside a 
freezer. 
</P>
<P>
	Deputies with the Marion County Sheriff's Department made the  
discovery around 10 a.m. after trying to arrest John Adams, who 
rented the house on Indianapolis' west side. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams, 24, is wanted on charges of holding up two restaurants.  
He remained at large Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The unidentified bodies, which had been wrapped separately, were  
taken to the city morgue for autopsies. 
</P>
<P>
	Indianapolis Police Sgt. Paul Ciesielski said he didn't know how  
long the bodies had been in the freezer or their cause of death. He 
said no additional charges have been filed against Adams. 
</P>
<P>
	``At this point, he's just wanted really for questioning for  
these deaths,'' he said. ``Obviously he's our main focus at this 
point.'' 
  	   	
