<HEADLINE> Cubs' Morandini Suspended Two Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Chicago Cubs second baseman Mickey Morandini was  
suspended two games and fined an undisclosed amount Wednesday by 
the National League for ``overly aggressive behavior'' toward an 
umpire. 
</P>
<P>
	The suspension is supposed to start with Thursday's game against  
the Pittsburgh Pirates, but Morandini can appeal. 
</P>
<P>
	Morandini and Cubs first base coach Dan Radison were both  
ejected in the seventh inning of a game against Milwaukee on Sept. 
17 for arguing a questionable out call at first base. 
</P>
<P>
	Morandini appeared to beat catcher Brian Banks' throw, but first  
base umpire Greg Gibson said he was out. Morandini then ran toward 
Gibson to argue the call and Radison tried to intercede before they 
were both tossed. 
  	   	
</P>
