<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Disasters Declared in Fla., Pa. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton opened the door Wednesday  
for more federal money to help storm cleanups in Florida, 
Pennsylvania and New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	He declared major disasters in all three states, which makes  
federal money available to local governments and individuals for 
repairs and loans. 
</P>
<P>
	In Florida, Clinton approved federal money to help repair or  
replace public facilities in nine counties that were hit by 
Hurricane Floyd last week. 
</P>
<P>
	In Pennsylvania, Clinton's declaration means business owners and  
others in four counties can apply for emergency disaster housing, 
grants, low-cost loans and other programs. The money covers damage 
from flash floods from Tropical Depression Dennis earlier this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
	In New Mexico, Clinton's declaration means local governments in  
six counties and on one Indian reservation can apply for money to 
replace public facilities damaged in severe storms and flooding in 
July and August. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
