<HEADLINE> Astros' Wagner Strains Elbow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Houston Astros reliever Billy Wagner has a  
slightly strained ligament in his left elbow and is listed as 
day-to-day. 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner, one of baseball's most dominating closers with his  
100-mph fastball and 37 saves, felt a twinge in the elbow while 
getting the final two outs in the eighth inning of the Astros' 6-3 
victory Tuesday in Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner was angry at not being allowed to pitch the ninth inning  
and get the save, but manager Larry Dierker said he wasn't about to 
risk exposing Wagner to a serious injury. 
</P>
<P>
	``The only one who thought he should go back out was Billy,''  
Dierker said. ``We're not going to take a chance, because we're not 
going anywhere without him.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner has converted 37 of 40 save opportunities, allowing only  
five hits while pitching 20 consecutive scoreless innings in 17 
games since Aug. 13. He has more saves than hits allowed (30). 
</P>
<P>
	The Astros, attempting to win a third consecutive NL Central  
title, have eight games remaining following Wednesday night's game 
in Pittsburgh. 
  	   	
</P>
