<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jerry Lewis Stalker Apologizes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- The man who spent more than four years in  
prison for stalking Jerry Lewis wants the comedian to know he's 
sorry. 
</P>
<P>
	``I apologize and it'll never happen again,'' Gary Benson said  
in a phone call to the syndicated ``Inside Edition'' television 
show on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Benson said he called Lewis about 12 times and went to his house  
a couple of times. He said he didn't realize his actions would have 
such an impact. 
</P>
<P>
	``I didn't think I did anything,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Benson, a 56-year-old diagnosed chronic schizophrenic, was  
convicted in 1995 of aggravated stalking and is scheduled to be 
released Oct. 5. 
</P>
<P>
	On Tuesday, a court granted Lewis' request to extend a 1992  
protection order against Benson until Sept. 21, 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	According to an affidavit, Lewis alleges Benson called him as  
recently as May and said, ``Jerry, I'll be out in 65 days.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Benson's attorney said his client plans to reside in another  
state upon his release. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
