<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Retired Orthodox Bishop Dead at 84 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Bishop Basil Rodzianko, the retired bishop of  
the Orthodox Church in America, is dead of cardiac arrest at age 
84. 
</P>
<P>
	He died Friday at his home in Washington.  
</P>
<P>
	For more than 30 years, the bishop made regular religious radio  
broadcasts from England and the United States to his native Russia 
and the Soviet Union. 
</P>
<P>
	He came to the United states from England in 1978 as bishop of  
Washington and of the Orthodox Church in America, which is an 
independent daughter church of the Russian Orthodox Church. 
</P>
<P>
	He later took on additional duties as bishop of San Francisco  
and the West and moved to San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
	He retired in 1984 and returned to Washington, but continued  
religious broadcasts via Voice of America and Vatican Radio. 
</P>
<P>
	Since 1991 he had made direct broadcasts on Russian national  
television during regular visits to Moscow. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
